-- Austrian Skier Hirscher Wins Opening Men’s World Cup Slalom
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-11-17T14:18:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-17/austrian-skier-hirscher-wins-opening-men-s-world-cup-slalom.html
World Cup skiing champion Marcel
Hirscher won the opening men’s slalom of the season, beating his
Austrian compatriot Mario Matt into second place.  Hirscher, who won the overall and slalom titles last
season, had an aggregate time of 1 minute, 45.42 seconds in
Levi,  Finland , 0.62 sec. faster than Matt.  Norway’s Henrik Kristoffersen, 19, came third, his first-ever top 10 spot.  Ted Ligety of the U.S., who won the opening men’s giant
slalom for a third straight year last month, was 11th today.  Yesterday, reigning world champion Mikaela Shiffrin of the
U.S. won the opening World Cup women’s slalom of the season in
Levi.  The 18-year-old beat  Germany ’s Maria Hoefl-Riesch by 1.06
seconds. Defending overall World Cup champion Tina Maze of
Slovenia was third.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at 
 celser@bloomberg.net  